0.9.27f - dom dic 16 14:21:49 CET 2001
--------------------------------------

 - The string quoting is more like Perl: single quoted
   strings (') are used literally (no backslash characters
   interpreted); the double quoted strings (") ones do,
   and variables (prefixed with $ as usual) are interpolated
   into.

 - Command line history (^P, ^N) in filp_console().

0.9.27e - lun dic 10 17:20:07 CET 2001
--------------------------------------

 - The 'false' command now pushes a NULL value instead
   of a 0 value; this had changed the comparison commands
   to return a NULL instead of a 0 on a non-true test.
   The 'while' command has also been changed to only
   exit the loop when the test block code returns NULL
   and not 0, a thing that was a source of all kinds
   of problems (as being unable to process a list with
   some zero values or even reading a 0 from a file).
   Anyway, this is a very serious change and can be
   a source to all kind of new problems. This version
   should be assumed as experimental.

 - Unification of the Unix and Win32 versions of the
   'glob' command so that they give the same results on both
   systems. A bug in the Unix version has also been fixed.

